   999000
   999001
   999002
!endblock

SKU of the master item for the option. The master item is one level up in the modular hierarchy, and must be one of the N<following:>

* An item in the products table (matching B<products.sku>)
* Another option in the options table (matching B<options.sku>)
* A {{CMD[jump="#options_phantom"]phantom}} item in the B<options> table.

If an option has a master item, then a customer cannot choose the option without having previously selected the master item.

The price for a master item is the sum of the item's price and the price for each of its subitems. Since the subitems are recursively defined, the top-level item reflects the aggregate price of the top-level price and all selected options.


